cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.SE

This paper deals with the security and privacy of computer systems, specifically the ability of malware to exfiltrate data from air-gapped computers. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the design considerations and evaluation of the acoustic channel, which suggests a possible fit for cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Additionally, the paper mentions the ability to leak data from different types of IT equipment and embedded systems, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses countermeasures, which could also fit under cs.SE (Software Engineering).
